func (p *ContainerPool) cleanup() {

                		
            

            
            

                638
                
                    
        p.mutex.Lock()

                		
            

            
            

                639
                
                    
        defer p.mutex.Unlock()

                		
            

            
            

                640
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                641
                
                    
        now := time.Now()

                		
            

            
            

                642
                
                    
        containersToRemove := make([]string, 0)

                		
            

            
            

                643
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                644
                
                    
        // Find containers that have been idle too long

                		
            

            
            

                645
                
                    
        for id, container := range p.containers {

                		
            

            
            

                646
                
                    
                if container.Status == types.ContainerStatusReady &&

                		
            

            
            

                647
                
                    
                        now.Sub(container.LastUsed) > p.config.IdleTimeout {

                		
            

            
            

                648
                
                    
                        containersToRemove = append(containersToRemove, id)

                		
            

            
            

                649
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                650
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                651
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                652
                
                    
        // Remove idle containers (but keep minimum number)

                		
            

            
            

                653
                
                    
        readyCount := p.getReadyContainerCount()

                		
            

            
            

                654
                
                    
        for _, id := range containersToRemove {

                		
            

            
            

                655
                
                    
                if readyCount <= p.config.MinContainers {

                		
            

            
            

                656
                
                    
                        break

                		
            

            
            

                657
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                658
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                659
                
                    
                if err := p.manager.CleanupContainer(context.Background(), id); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                660
                
                    
                        p.logger.Warnf("Failed to cleanup container %s: %v", id, err)

                		
            

            
            

                661
                
                    
                        continue

                		
            

            
            

                662
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                663
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                664
                
                    
                delete(p.containers, id)

                		
            

            
            

                665
                
                    
                readyCount--

                		
            

            
            

                666
                
                    
                p.stats.DestroyedCount++

                		
            

            
            

                667
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                668
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                669
                
                    
        if len(containersToRemove) > 0 {

                		
            

            
            

                670
                
                    
                p.logger.Infof("Cleaned up %d idle containers from %s language pool", len(containersToRemove), p.language)

                		
            

            
            

                671

                672
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                673

                675

func (ep *ExecutionPipeline) updateStats(success bool, duration time.Duration, complexity float64) {

                		
            

            
            

                241
                
                    
        ep.mutex.Lock()

                		
            

            
            

                242
                
                    
        defer ep.mutex.Unlock()

                		
            

            
            

                243
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                244
                
                    
        ep.stats.TotalExecutions++

                		
            

            
            

                245
                
                    
        ep.stats.LastExecution = time.Now()

                		
            

            
            

                246
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                247
                
                    
        if success {

                		
            

            
            

                248
                
                    
                ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions++

                		
            

            
            

                249
                
                    
        } else {

                		
            

            
            

                250
                
                    
                ep.stats.FailedExecutions++

                		
            

            
            

                251
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                252
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                253
                
                    
        // Update execution time statistics

                		
            

            
            

                254
                
                    
        if ep.stats.MinExecutionTime == 0 || duration < ep.stats.MinExecutionTime {

                		
            

            
            

                255
                
                    
                ep.stats.MinExecutionTime = duration

                		
            

            
            

                256
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                257
                
                    
        if duration > ep.stats.MaxExecutionTime {

                		
            

            
            

                258
                
                    
                ep.stats.MaxExecutionTime = duration

                		
            

            
            

                259
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                260
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                261
                
                    
        // Calculate average execution time - only if we have successful executions

                		
            

            
            

                262
                
                    
        if ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions > 0 {

                		
            

            
            

                263
                
                    
                if ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions == 1 {

                		
            

            
            

                264
                
                    
                        // First successful execution

                		
            

            
            

                265
                
                    
                        ep.stats.AverageExecutionTime = duration

                		
            

            
            

                266
                
                    
                } else {

                		
            

            
            

                267
                
                    
                        // Calculate running average

                		
            

            
            

                268
                
                    
                        totalDuration := ep.stats.AverageExecutionTime * time.Duration(ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions-1)

                		
            

            
            

                269
                
                    
                        totalDuration += duration

                		
            

            
            

                270
                
                    
                        ep.stats.AverageExecutionTime = totalDuration / time.Duration(ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions)

                		
            

            
            

                271
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                272
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                273
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                274
                
                    
        // Update cost statistics

                		
            

            
            

                275
                
                    
        cost := ep.calculateCost(duration, complexity)

                		
            

            
            

                276
                
                    
        ep.stats.TotalCost += cost

                		
            

            
            

                277
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                278
                
                    
        // Calculate average cost - only if we have successful executions

                		
            

            
            

                279
                
                    
        if ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions > 0 {

                		
            

            
            

                280
                
                    
                ep.stats.AverageCost = ep.stats.TotalCost / float64(ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions)

                		
            

            
            

                281
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                282
                
                    
}

func (em *ExecutionMonitor) GetHealthStatus() *HealthStatus {

                		
            

            
            

                149
                
                    
        em.mutex.RLock()

                		
            

            
            

                150
                
                    
        defer em.mutex.RUnlock()

                		
            

            
            

                151
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                152
                
                    
        // Calculate overall health score

                		
            

            
            

                153
                
                    
        healthScore := 100.0

                		
            

            
            

                154
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                155
                
                    
        // Reduce score based on alerts

                		
            

            
            

                156
                
                    
        criticalAlerts := 0

                		
            

            
            

                157
                
                    
        warningAlerts := 0

                		
            

            
            

                158
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                159
                
                    
        for _, alert := range em.alerts {

                		
            

            
            

                160
                
                    
                if time.Since(alert.Timestamp) < time.Hour { // Only consider recent alerts

                		
            

            
            

                161
                
                    
                        switch alert.Severity {

                		
            

            
            

                162
                
                    
                        case "error":

                		
            

            
            

                163
                
                    
                                criticalAlerts++

                		
            

            
            

                164
                
                    
                        case "warning":

                		
            

            
            

                165
                
                    
                                warningAlerts++

                		
            

            
            

                166
                
                    
                        }

                		
            

            
            

                167
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                168
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                169
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                170
                
                    
        healthScore -= float64(criticalAlerts) * 20 // Each critical alert reduces score by 20

                		
            

            
            

                171
                
                    
        healthScore -= float64(warningAlerts) * 5   // Each warning alert reduces score by 5

                		
            

            
            

                172
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                173
                
                    
        if healthScore < 0 {

                		
            

            
            

                174
                
                    
                healthScore = 0

                		
            

            
            

                175
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                176
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                177
                
                    
        status := "healthy"

                		
            

            
            

                178
                
                    
        if healthScore < 50 {

                		
            

            
            

                179
                
                    
                status = "critical"

                		
            

            
            

                180
                
                    
        } else if healthScore < 80 {

                		
            

            
            

                181
                
                    
                status = "warning"

                		
            

            
            

                182
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                183
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                184
                
                    
        return &HealthStatus{

                		
            

            
            

                185
                
                    
                Status:    status,

                		
            

            
            

                186
                
                    
                Score:     healthScore,

                		
            

            
            

                187
                
                    
                LastCheck: time.Now(),

                		
            

            
            

                188
                
                    
                Alerts:    em.getRecentAlerts(),

                		
            

            
            

                189
                
                    
                Metrics:   em.metrics,

                		
            

            
            

                190
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                191
                
                    
}

func (ep *ExecutionPipeline) Execute(ctx context.Context, fileURL string, noOfAttesters int) (*types.ExecutionResult, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                48
                
                    
        startTime := time.Now()

                		
            

            
            

                49
                
                    
        executionID := generateExecutionID()

                		
            

            
            

                50
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                51
                
                    
        ep.logger.Infof("Starting execution %s for file: %s", executionID, fileURL)

                		
            

            
            

                52
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                53
                
                    
        // Create execution context

                		
            

            
            

                54
                
                    
        execCtx := &types.ExecutionContext{

                		
            

            
            

                55
                
                    
                FileURL:       fileURL,

                		
            

            
            

                56
                
                    
                NoOfAttesters: noOfAttesters,

                		
            

            
            

                57
                
                    
                TraceID:       executionID,

                		
            

            
            

                58
                
                    
                StartedAt:     startTime,

                		
            

            
            

                59
                
                    
                Metadata:      make(map[string]string),

                		
            

            
            

                60
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                61
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                62
                
                    
        // Track execution

                		
            

            
            

                63
                
                    
        ep.mutex.Lock()

                		
            

            
            

                64
                
                    
        ep.activeExecutions[executionID] = execCtx

                		
            

            
            

                65
                
                    
        ep.mutex.Unlock()

                		
            

            
            

                66
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                67
                
                    
        defer func() {

                		
            

            
            

                68
                
                    
                // Remove from active executions

                		
            

            
            

                69
                
                    
                ep.mutex.Lock()

                		
            

            
            

                70
                
                    
                delete(ep.activeExecutions, executionID)

                		
            

            
            

                71
                
                    
                ep.mutex.Unlock()

                		
            

            
            

                72
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                73
                
                    
                // Update statistics

                		
            

            
            

                74
                
                    
                duration := time.Since(startTime)

                		
            

            
            

                75
                
                    
                ep.updateStats(true, duration, 0.0)

                		
            

            
            

                76
                
                    
        }()

                		
            

            
            

                77
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                78
                
                    
        // Execute pipeline stages

                		
            

            
            

                79
                
                    
        result, err := ep.executeStages(ctx, execCtx)

                		
            

            
            

                80
                
                    
        if err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                81
                
                    
                execCtx.CompletedAt = time.Now()

                		
            

            
            

                82
                
                    
                ep.updateStats(false, time.Since(startTime), 0.0)

                		
            

            
            

                83
                
                    
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("execution failed: %w", err)

                		
            

            
            

                84
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                85
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                86
                
                    
        execCtx.CompletedAt = time.Now()

                		
            

            
            

                87
                
                    
        duration := time.Since(startTime)

                		
            

            
            

                88
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                89
                
                    
        ep.logger.Infof("Execution %s completed successfully in %v", executionID, duration)

                		
            

            
            

                90
                
                    
        return result, nil

                		
            

            
            

                91
                
                    
}

func (em *ExecutionMonitor) GetAlerts(severity string, limit int) []Alert {

                		
            

            
            

                207
                
                    
        em.mutex.RLock()

                		
            

            
            

                208
                
                    
        defer em.mutex.RUnlock()

                		
            

            
            

                209
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                210
                
                    
        filteredAlerts := make([]Alert, 0)

                		
            

            
            

                211
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                212
                
                    
        for _, alert := range em.alerts {

                		
            

            
            

                213
                
                    
                if severity == "" || alert.Severity == severity {

                		
            

            
            

                214
                
                    
                        filteredAlerts = append(filteredAlerts, alert)

                		
            

            
            

                215
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                216
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                217
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                218
                
                    
        // Sort by timestamp (newest first)

                		
            

            
            

                219
                
                    
        for i := 0; i < len(filteredAlerts)-1; i++ {

                		
            

            
            

                220
                
                    
                for j := i + 1; j < len(filteredAlerts); j++ {

                		
            

            
            

                221
                
                    
                        if filteredAlerts[i].Timestamp.Before(filteredAlerts[j].Timestamp) {

                		
            

            
            

                222
                
                    
                                filteredAlerts[i], filteredAlerts[j] = filteredAlerts[j], filteredAlerts[i]

                		
            

            
            

                223
                
                    
                        }

                		
            

            
            

                224
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                225
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                226
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                227
                
                    
        // Apply limit

                		
            

            
            

                228
                
                    
        if limit > 0 && len(filteredAlerts) > limit {

                		
            

            
            

                229
                
                    
                filteredAlerts = filteredAlerts[:limit]

                		
            

            
            

                230
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                231
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                232
                
                    
        return filteredAlerts

                		
            

            
            

                233
                
                    
}

func (ep *ExecutionPipeline) calculateFees(execCtx *types.ExecutionContext) float64 {

                		
            

            
            

                174

                175

                180

                182
                
                    
                // Parse complexity and apply factor

                		
            

            
            

                183
                
                    
                // This is a simplified calculation

                185
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                186
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                187

func (ep *ExecutionPipeline) calculateCost(duration time.Duration, complexity float64) float64 {

                		
            

            
            

                285
                
                    
        // Basic cost calculation based on execution time and complexity

                		
            

            
            

                286
                
                    
        timeCost := duration.Seconds() * ep.config.GetFeesConfig().PricePerTG

                		
            

            
            

                287
                
                    
        complexityCost := complexity * ep.config.GetFeesConfig().PricePerTG

                		
            

            
            

                288
                
                    
        return timeCost + complexityCost + ep.config.GetFeesConfig().FixedCost

                		
            

            
            

                289
                
                    
}

func (v *codeValidator) calculateContentComplexity(content []byte) float64 {

                		
            

            
            

                188
                
                    
        // Handle empty content

                		
            

            
            

                189
                
                    
        if len(content) == 0 {

                		
            

            
            

                190
                
                    
                return 0.0

                		
            

            
            

                191
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                192
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                193
                
                    
        contentStr := string(content)

                		
            

            
            

                194
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                195
                
                    
        // Basic complexity calculation based on:

                		
            

            
            

                196
                
                    
        // 1. File size (in KB)

                		
            

            
            

                197
                
                    
        // 2. Number of lines

                		
            

            
            

                198
                
                    
        // 3. Number of functions

                		
            

            
            

                199
                
                    
        // 4. Number of imports

                		
            

            
            

                200
                
                    
        // 5. Number of loops and conditionals

                		
            

            
            

                201
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                202

                203

                204
                
                    
        numLines := float64(len(lines))

                		
            

            
            

                205
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                206

                207

                208
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                209
                
                    
        // Count imports

                		
            

            
            

                210

                211
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                212
                
                    
        // Count loops and conditionals

                215
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                216
                
                    
        // Calculate complexity score

                		
            

            
            

                217
                
                    
        complexity := sizeKB*0.1 + // Size factor

                		
            

            
            

                218
                
                    
                numLines*0.01 + // Line count factor

                		
            

            
            

                219
                
                    
                functionCount*0.5 + // Function factor

                		
            

            
            

                220
                
                    
                importCount*0.2 + // Import factor

                		
            

            
            

                221
                
                    
                (loopCount+conditionalCount)*0.3 // Control flow factor

                		
            

            
            

                222
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                223
                
                    
        return complexity

                		
            

            
            

                224

func (c *fileCache) accessCachedFile(cachedFile *cachedFile) (string, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                110

func (c *fileCache) ensureSpace(requiredSize int64) error {

                		
            

            
            

                186
                
                    
        c.mutex.Lock()

                		
            

            
            

                187
                
                    
        defer c.mutex.Unlock()

                		
            

            
            

                188
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                189
                
                    
        // If we have enough space, no need to evict

                		
            

            
            

                190
                
                    
        if c.stats.Size+requiredSize <= c.config.MaxCacheSize {

                		
            

            
            

                191
                
                    
                return nil

                		
            

            
            

                192
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                193
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                194
                
                    
        // Need to evict files

                		
            

            
            

                195
                
                    
        evictionSize := c.stats.Size + requiredSize - c.config.MaxCacheSize

                		
            

            
            

                196
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                197
                
                    
        // Sort files by last accessed time (oldest first)

                		
            

            
            

                198
                
                    
        type fileEntry struct {

                		
            

            
            

                199
                
                    
                hash string

                		
            

            
            

                200
                
                    
                file *cachedFile

                		
            

            
            

                201
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                202
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                203
                
                    
        var files []fileEntry

                		
            

            
            

                204
                
                    
        for hash, file := range c.fileCache {

                		
            

            
            

                205
                
                    
                files = append(files, fileEntry{hash: hash, file: file})

                		
            

            
            

                206
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                207
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                208
                
                    
        // Sort by last accessed time (oldest first)

                		
            

            
            

                209
                
                    
        for i := 0; i < len(files)-1; i++ {

                		
            

            
            

                210
                
                    
                for j := i + 1; j < len(files); j++ {

                		
            

            
            

                211
                
                    
                        if files[i].file.LastAccessed.After(files[j].file.LastAccessed) {

                		
            

            
            

                212
                
                    
                                files[i], files[j] = files[j], files[i]

                		
            

            
            

                213
                
                    
                        }

                		
            

            
            

                214
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                215
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                216
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                217
                
                    
        // Evict files until we have enough space

                		
            

            
            

                218
                
                    
        evictedSize := int64(0)

                		
            

            
            

                219
                
                    
        for _, entry := range files {

                		
            

            
            

                220
                
                    
                if evictedSize >= evictionSize {

                		
            

            
            

                221
                
                    
                        break

                		
            

            
            

                222
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                223
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                224
                
                    
                // Remove file from disk

                		
            

            
            

                225
                
                    
                if err := c.fs.Remove(entry.file.Path); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                226
                
                    
                        c.logger.Warnf("Failed to remove cached file: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                227
                
                    
                        continue

                		
            

            
            

                228
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                229
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                230
                
                    
                // Remove from cache

                		
            

            
            

                231
                
                    
                delete(c.fileCache, entry.hash)

                		
            

            
            

                232
                
                    
                evictedSize += entry.file.Size

                		
            

            
            

                233
                
                    
                c.stats.EvictionCount++

                		
            

            
            

                234
                
                    
                c.stats.ItemCount--

                		
            

            
            

                235
                
                    
                c.stats.Size -= entry.file.Size

                		
            

            
            

                236
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                237
                
                    
                c.logger.Debugf("Evicted cached file: %s (size: %d bytes)", entry.hash, entry.file.Size)

                		
            

            
            

                238
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                239
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                240
                
                    
        c.logger.Infof("Evicted %d bytes (%d files) from cache", evictedSize, c.stats.EvictionCount)

                		
            

            
            

                241
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                242
                
                    
        // Save updated metadata after eviction

                		
            

            
            

                243
                
                    
        if err := c.saveMetadata(); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                244
                
                    
                c.logger.Warnf("Failed to save cache metadata after eviction: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                245
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                246
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                247
                
                    
        return nil

                		
            

            
            

                248
                
                    
}

func (c *fileCache) storeFile(key string, content []byte) (string, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                145

                147

                152

                155

                156

                161

func (c *HTTPClient) DoWithRetry(req *http.Request) (*http.Response, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                99
                
                    
        // Prepare request body for retries

                		
            

            
            

                100
                
                    
        var getBody func() (io.ReadCloser, error)

                		
            

            
            

                101
                
                    
        if req.GetBody != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                102
                
                    
                getBody = req.GetBody

                		
            

            
            

                103
                
                    
        } else if req.Body != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                104
                
                    
                // Fallback for requests without GetBody

                		
            

            
            

                105
                
                    
                bodyBytes, err := io.ReadAll(req.Body)

                		
            

            
            

                106
                
                    
                if err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                107
                
                    
                        return nil, fmt.Errorf("error reading request body: %w", err)

                		
            

            
            

                108
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                109
                
                    
                if err := req.Body.Close(); err != nil {

                111

                112

                113
                
                    
                getBody = func() (io.ReadCloser, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                114
                
                    
                        return io.NopCloser(bytes.NewBuffer(bodyBytes)), nil

                		
            

            
            

                115

                117
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                118

                119
                
                    
        operation := func() (*http.Response, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                120
                
                    
                // Clone the request for each attempt

                		
            

            
            

                121
                
                    
                reqClone := req.Clone(req.Context())

                		
            

            
            

                122
                
                    
                if getBody != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                123
                
                    
                        body, err := getBody()

func (c *ipfsClient) Upload(filename string, data []byte) (string, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                85
                
                    
        if filename == "" {

                		
            

            
            

                86
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("filename cannot be empty")

                		
            

            
            

                87
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                88
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                89

                91

                92
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                93
                
                    
        body := &bytes.Buffer{}

                		
            

            
            

                94
                
                    
        writer := multipart.NewWriter(body)

                		
            

            
            

                95
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                96
                
                    
        // Add the "network" field and set it to "public" to ensure content is publicly accessible

                		
            

            
            

                97
                
                    
        if err := writer.WriteField("network", "public"); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                98
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to write network field: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                99
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                100
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                101
                
                    
        // Add the file

                		
            

            
            

                102
                
                    
        part, err := writer.CreateFormFile("file", filename)

                		
            

            
            

                103
                
                    
        if err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                104
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to create form file: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                105
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                106
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                107
                
                    
        if _, err := part.Write(data); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                108
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to write data to form: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                109
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                110
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                111
                
                    
        if err := writer.Close(); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                112
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to close writer: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                113

                117

                118
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to create request: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                119
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                120
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                121
                
                    
        req.Header.Set("Authorization", "Bearer "+c.config.PinataJWT)

                		
            

            
            

                122

                123
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                124
                
                    
        // Send request

                		
            

            
            

                125
                
                    
        resp, err := c.httpClient.DoWithRetry(req)

                		
            

            
            

                126
                
                    
        if err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                127
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to send request: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                128
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                129
                
                    
        defer func() {

                		
            

            
            

                130
                
                    
                if err := resp.Body.Close(); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                131
                
                    
                        c.logger.Warn("Failed to close response body", "error", err)

                		
            

            
            

                132
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                133
                
                    
        }()

                		
            

            
            

                134
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                135
                
                    
        if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {

                		
            

            
            

                136
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("http error: status code %d", resp.StatusCode)

                141
                
                    
        if err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                142
                
                    
                return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to read response body: %v", err)

                		
            

            
            

                143
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                144
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                145
                
                    
        // Parse response

                		
            

            
            

                146
                
                    
        var ipfsResponse struct {

                		
            

            
            

                147
                
                    
                Data struct {

                		
            

            
            

                148
                
                    
                        CID string `json:"cid"`

func customColorLevelEncoder(level zapcore.Level, enc zapcore.PrimitiveArrayEncoder) {

                		
            

            
            

                109
                
                    
        var color string

                		
            

            
            

                110
                
                    
        var levelStr string

func NewZapLogger(config LoggerConfig) (*zapLogger, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                18
                
                    
        fileName := fmt.Sprintf("%s.log", time.Now().Format("2006-01-02"))

                		
            

            
            

                19
                
                    
        fullPath := filepath.Join(BaseDataDir, LogsDir, string(config.ProcessName), fileName)

                21
                
                    
        // File writer with sequential rotation and no colors

                		
            

            
            

                22
                
                    
        rotator := NewSequentialRotator(

                		
            

            
            

                23
                
                    
                fullPath,

                50,    // MaxSize in MB

                30,    // MaxAge in days

                		
            

            
            

                26
                
                    
                1000,  // MaxBackups (number of old files to keep)

                		
            

            
            

                27
                
                    
                false, // Compress (disabled for now for Loki compatibility)

                		
            

            
            

                28
                
                    
        )

                		
            

            
            

                29
                
                    
        fileWriter := zapcore.AddSync(rotator)

                		
            

            
            

                30
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                31
                
                    
        // Console output (with colors)

                		
            

            
            

                32
                
                    
        consoleWriter := zapcore.AddSync(os.Stdout)

                		
            

            
            

                33
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                34
                
                    
        // Create cores

                		
            

            
            

                35
                
                    
        fileCore := zapcore.NewCore(

                		
            

            
            

                36
                
                    
                plainFileEncoder(),

                fileWriter,

                		
            

            
            

                38
                
                    
                zapcore.DebugLevel,

                		
            

            
            

                39
                
                    
        )

                		
            

            
            

                40
                
                    
        consoleCore := zapcore.NewCore(

                		
            

            
            

                41
                
                    
                coloredConsoleEncoder(),

                		
            

            
            

                42
                
                    
                consoleWriter,

                		
            

            
            

                43
                
                    
                getLogLevel(config.IsDevelopment),

                		
            

            
            

                44
                
                    
        )

                		
            

            
            

                45
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                46
                
                    
        // Combine cores

        // Build the logger

                54
                
                    
        )

                		
            

            
            

                55
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                56
                
                    
        return &zapLogger{

                sugarLogger: logger.Sugar(),

                198

func (r *SequentialRotator) rotate() error {

                		
            

            
            

                104
                
                    
        // Close current file

                		
            

            
            

                105
                
                    
        if r.file != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                106
                
                    
                if err := r.file.Close(); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                107
                
                    
                        return err

                		
            

            
            

                108
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                109
                
                    
                r.file = nil

                		
            

            
            

                110
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                111
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                112
                
                    
        // Get the next sequence number

                		
            

            
            

                113
                
                    
        nextSeq := r.getNextSequenceNumber()

                		
            

            
            

                114
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                115
                
                    
        // Generate new filename with sequence number

                		
            

            
            

                116
                
                    
        base := strings.TrimSuffix(r.filename, ".log")

                		
            

            
            

                117
                
                    
        rotatedName := fmt.Sprintf("%s.%d.log", base, nextSeq)

                		
            

            
            

                118
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                119
                
                    
        // Rename current file to rotated name

                		
            

            
            

                120
                
                    
        if err := os.Rename(r.filename, rotatedName); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                121
                
                    
                return err

                		
            

            
            

                122
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                123
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                124
                
                    
        // Clean up old files

                		
            

            
            

                125
                
                    
        r.cleanupOldFiles()

                		
            

            
            

                126
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                127
                
                    
        // Open new file

                		
            

            
            

                128
                
                    
        r.size = 0

                		
            

            
            

                129
                
                    
        return r.openFile()

                		
            

            
            

                130
                
                    
}

func GenerateProof(ipfsData types.IPFSData, connState *tls.ConnectionState) (types.ProofData, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                109
                
                    
        // Validate inputs

                		
            

            
            

                110
                
                    
        if connState == nil {

                		
            

            
            

                111

                112

                113
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                114
                
                    
        if len(connState.PeerCertificates) == 0 {

                		
            

            
            

                115
                
                    
                return types.ProofData{}, errors.New("no TLS certificates found in connection state")

                		
            

            
            

                116

                117
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                118

                120
                
                    
        if err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                121
                
                    
                return types.ProofData{}, fmt.Errorf("failed to stringify IPFS data: %w", err)

                		
            

            
            

                122
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                123
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                124
                
                    
        // Validate and process the first certificate

                		
            

            
            

                125
                
                    
        cert := connState.PeerCertificates[0]

                		
            

            
            

                126
                
                    
        if cert == nil {

                		
            

            
            

                127
                
                    
                return types.ProofData{}, errors.New("first peer certificate is nil")

                		
            

            
            

                128

                129
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                130

                131

                132
                
                    
                return types.ProofData{}, fmt.Errorf("certificate validation failed: %w", err)

                		
            

            
            

                133

                134
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                135
                
                    
        // Hash the certificate

                		
            

            
            

                136

                137

                138
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                139

                140

                142
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                143

                144

                145

                146

                149

func Retry[T any](ctx context.Context, operation func() (T, error), retryConfig *RetryConfig, logger logging.Logger) (T, error) {

                		
            

            
            

                92
                
                    
        var zero T

                		
            

            
            

                93
                
                    
        var err error

                		
            

            
            

                94
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                95
                
                    
        if retryConfig == nil {

                		
            

            
            

                96
                
                    
                retryConfig = DefaultRetryConfig()

                		
            

            
            

                97
                
                    
        } else if err := retryConfig.Validate(); err != nil {

                		
            

            
            

                98
                
                    
                return zero, fmt.Errorf("invalid retry config: %w", err)

                		
            

            
            

                99
                
                    
        }

                		
            

            
            

                100
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                101
                
                    
        delay := retryConfig.InitialDelay

                		
            

            
            

                102
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                103
                
                    
        for attempt := 0; attempt < retryConfig.MaxRetries; attempt++ {

                		
            

            
            

                104
                
                    
                select {

                		
            

            
            

                105
                
                    
                case <-ctx.Done():

                		
            

            
            

                106
                
                    
                        return zero, ctx.Err()

                		
            

            
            

                107
                
                    
                default:

                		
            

            
            

                108
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                109
                
                    

                		
            

            
            

                110
                
                    
                result, opErr := operation()

                		
            

            
            

                111
                
                    
                if opErr == nil {

                		
            

            
            

                112
                
                    
                        return result, nil

                		
            

            
            

                113
                
                    
                }

                		
            

            
            

                114
